By Chinyere Omeire  Lagos  –  A 25-year-old sales representative, Chioma Success, who allegedly stole her employer’s goods worth N250, 000, on Monday appeared before an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. Success, whose address was not provided, is facing a count charge of stealing, to which she pleaded not guilty. The Prosecutor, Sgt. Cyriacus Osuji, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on July 6 at 8:32p.m. at Shop No. GF 37, Mandilas building, Lagos Island. Osuji said that the defendant stole some Jean trousers valued at N250, 000, from the complainant, Mr Emmanuel Eze-Okafor. He said the offence contravened Section 287(7) of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that section provides seven years imprisonment for stealing from one’s employer. The Magistrate, Mrs A. O. Erile, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N100, 000 with two sureties in like sum. She ordered that the sureties must be gainfully employed, with evidence of tax payments to the Lagos State Government. Erile adjourned the case until Aug. 14 for mention. (NAN) By Chinyere Omeire Lagos - A 26-year-old man Matthew Edet, was on Tuesday arraigned in an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, for allegedly burgling his employer’s house and stealing property worth N14.5 million. The defendant whose residential address was not given, is facing trial on a 20-count charge, bordering on conspiracy,… October 29, 2019 In "Metro" LAGOS - The Police on Monday arraigned three men in an Ogudu Chief Magistrates’ Court for conspiring to commit burglary and stealing of N796, 700. The defendants are Ajala Oshinowo, 22, Patrick Nwauzo, 30, and Owoduni Oshinowo, 36, all of Adebayo Street, Alapere in Lagos State. They are facing a… February 16, 2015 In "News" By Sandra Umeh Lagos - The Police in Lagos have charged a 37-years-old man, Ikechukwu Mba, in an Ojo Magistrates’ court in Lagos for allegedly stealing Wall Bracket lights valued N700,000. The defendant 